comment_data.body:
OK, this (meant to be constructive) issue has become a dumping ground for complaints, so I'm taking the liberty of locking it. If you have questions or concerns, you are welcome to air them on Matrix.

To summarize:

* the original legacy _implementation_ was broken in Neovim and impossible to maintain, so it had to be removed (even if you personally didn't use any modern enough features of Neovim to notice);
* we do want to bring back the _functionality_ of printing styled buffer contents in a more flexible and maintainable form (i.e., as a bundled Lua plugin; if that requires hooks in the C sources, those can be added of course);
* but this requires somebody who actually cares about this functionality to drive this and open a PR; for the project itself this is on the very bottom of the (already over-long) priority list as none of the maintainers used it or see any value for themselves.
